tions about the social life of the city and for urban research more generally. Essential for a broad range of urban studies scholars, this book is an invaluable teaching resource and a useful tool for policy-makers and planners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCities and townszChina. 0aSociology, UrbanzChina. 0aUrbanizationzChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh1 aChen, Juan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForrest, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForrest, Ray, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGransow, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Zhigang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Shuo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLui, Tai-lok, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNijman, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOu, Shunxian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Donnell, Mary Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRen, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRen, Julie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRen, Xuefei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Zheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWissink, Bart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWissink, Bart, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWu, Fulong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWu, Rong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aXie, S